      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 36: Only `increaseRampTime` is validated, but several config values can make the controller behave incorrectly if a caller supplies a custom `Config`: `minBitrateKbps \u003e maxBitrateKbps`, `initialBitrateKbps` outside limits, negative alpha values, negative cooldown/probe values, or `maxDecreaseFactor \u003e 1`. That can lead to invalid clamp bounds, negative timing comparisons, or increases/decreases outside the intended AIMD envelope. Normalize all externally configurable fields in the constructor before initializing state.\n```suggestion\ncfg_.lossAlpha \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.lossAlpha, 0.0f, 1.0f);\ncfg_.rttAlpha \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.rttAlpha, 0.0f, 1.0f);\ncfg_.maxDecreaseFactor \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.maxDecreaseFactor, 0.0f, 1.0f);\ncfg_.minIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.minIncreaseFactor, 0.0f);\ncfg_.maxIncreaseFactor \u003d std::max(cfg_.maxIncreaseFactor, cfg_.minIncreaseFactor);\ncfg_.decreaseCooldownSec \u003d std::max(cfg_.decreaseCooldownSec, 0.0f);\ncfg_.probeDelaySec \u003d std::max(cfg_.probeDelaySec, 0.0f);\nif (cfg_.minBitrateKbps \u003e cfg_.maxBitrateKbps)\n    std::swap(cfg_.minBitrateKbps, cfg_.maxBitrateKbps);\ncfg_.initialBitrateKbps \u003d std::clamp(cfg_.initialBitrateKbps, cfg_.minBitrateKbps, cfg_.maxBitrateKbps);\n```",
