      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🔴 Critical Issues - Must fix before merge] Line 663: The controller is updated from RTCP RR only after `sinceRestart \u003e\u003d 2.0f`, but `lastMediaRestart_` is no longer refreshed when bitrate changes. The old loss path set `lastMediaRestart_ \u003d now` on decrease, effectively suppressing stale RTCP reports after each encoder restart/bitrate change. With the new flow, immediately following `setNewBitrate()` the next RR can still reflect the pre-change bitrate and trigger another decrease, causing cascaded bitrate drops. Update the restart/stale-report timestamp when the encoder bitrate actually changes, or add a dedicated `lastBitrateChange_` guard used by `adaptQualityAndBitrate()`.\n```suggestion\nif (videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent !\u003d newBR) {\n    videoBitrateInfo_.videoBitrateCurrent \u003d newBR;\n    lastMediaRestart_ \u003d clock::now();\n    storeVideoBitrateInfo();\n```\nUse a separate timestamp if `lastMediaRestart_` has broader semantics.",
