      "side": 1,
      "message": "[🟡 Suggestions - Improvements to consider] Line 715: `setupVideoBitrateInfo()` calls `bwController_.setLimits()` on every RTCP cycle, but `setLimits()` only clamps `targetBitrate_` and leaves `lastStableBitrate_` unchanged. If codec limits are reduced, `lastStableBitrate_` can remain above the new maximum, which skews the probing logic that compares `targetBitrate_` against `lastStableBitrate_ * 85 / 100`. Clamp `lastStableBitrate_` when limits change.\n```suggestion\ncfg_.minBitrateKbps \u003d minKbps;\ncfg_.maxBitrateKbps \u003d maxKbps;\ntargetBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(targetBitrate_);\nlastStableBitrate_ \u003d clampBitrate(lastStableBitrate_);\n```",
